Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.39,0:00:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I can't do it." "It's too frustrating."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.02,0:00:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Break down those hurdles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.19,0:00:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is nothing I can't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.36,0:00:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is being manipulated on the field?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.87,0:00:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not frightened yet I get told to go away...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The path to the unseen future...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.92,0:00:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I may not be able to choose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.47,0:00:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Close your eyes, and shuffle your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.56,0:01:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Definitely, just like cards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.31,0:01:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As promised, yes! you are the winner
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.31,0:01:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Never lose! Shuffle your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}definitely, just like cards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.78,0:01:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ever since that miracle...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.06,0:01:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Malik's Opening Play:\N The God Combo"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.51,0:01:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.35,0:01:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why didn't you take the {\c&H0856C0&}Great Moth{\r} card?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it much more of a Rare Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.35,0:01:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't know about this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.90,0:01:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have {\c&H0856C0&}Larvae Moth{\r} or {\c&H0856C0&}Cocoon of Evolution{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.99,0:01:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, even if I took {\c&H0856C0&}Great Moth{\r}, I couldn't use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:01:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you ask me,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.37,0:02:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after taking away Haga-kun's Puzzle Card, you just {\i1}couldn't{\i0} take his {\c&H0856C0&}Great Moth{\r} too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's not it...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.67,0:02:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.30,0:02:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi is becoming quite the Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi better watch himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No~!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that's the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.51,0:02:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.81,0:02:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what he's up to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.06,0:02:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.48,0:02:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's find you another Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.23,0:02:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.57,0:02:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll definitely become a True Duelist and challenge you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.18,0:03:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but that friend of you guys, Mutou Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.10,0:03:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the hateful Pharaoh who destroyed our tribe will soon die!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.81,0:03:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Doll is ready to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.40,0:03:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I'm about to control the Doll and battle against the Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}kill{\i0} the Pharaoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.41,0:03:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.08,0:03:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does this person think he's cool in that outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.71,0:03:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.17,0:03:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't moved even an inch in over two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it even human~?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.56,0:03:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.33,0:03:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.61,0:03:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:03:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.95,0:04:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To where Yugi is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what it is you're fighting for in Battle City.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is your memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know from the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but why would you enter this tournament if you weren't after Rare Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you really wanted to find something important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.49,0:04:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little, I tried again and again to solve the Millennium Puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.92,0:04:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was able to meet an important person like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted friends, and you gave me courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.18,0:05:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I've met many companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.60,0:05:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.35,0:05:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}It was your own strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.73,0:05:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why this time, I'll lend {\i1}you{\i0} my strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll fight together...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.15,0:05:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,though I may not be able to do much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.86,0:05:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}That's not true at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.49,0:05:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Because you're by my side, I'm able to do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.91,0:05:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Now and forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.18,0:05:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's coming...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:05:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vessel Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.44,0:05:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:05:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.82,0:06:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.86,0:06:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one controlling this doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this Silent Doll is merely an empty shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Empty shell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.79,0:06:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. With the power of my Millennium Rod,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.13,0:06:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This pantomime has severed all ties with emotion in his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, this is no longer a being standing before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no different than scrap.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.89,0:06:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're misusing the power of the Millennium Items for your own gain!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.94,0:06:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.36,0:06:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a battle that's been destined for 3,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.20,0:06:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this Duel is destined, I have no choice but to accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.20,0:06:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.83,0:06:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my true enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.46,0:06:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I win this Duel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.59,0:07:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this doll will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.42,0:07:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where you run, this doll will chase you until it kills you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's {\i1}if{\i0} you can beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}He has a God Card with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(100,100)}God Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll defeat God!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.16,0:07:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A battle involving the Pharaoh from 3,000 years ago is repeating itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.67,0:07:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the future I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.46,0:07:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those involved in this destiny have been called to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Millennium Ring is showing me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.39,0:07:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Millennium Item has appeared in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the wielder lies within here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.27,0:08:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's coming...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.41,0:08:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They escaped...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.17,0:08:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this palette?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no clue what's about to happen in this city,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.43,0:08:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.97,0:08:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me join in as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.48,0:08:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also being driven by the fate resolving around the Millennium Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.53,0:08:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.19,0:08:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I figured, you're coming, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Move and let me pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.33,0:08:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can you really use your Millennium Rod against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.25,0:09:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it's for the sake of our future, then I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.25,0:09:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if it's you, dear sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.13,0:09:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew I should have tried harder to stop you back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.02,0:09:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When the two of us meet again....
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.14,0:09:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will we fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.02,0:09:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.07,0:09:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And after I beat you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.03,0:09:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll go after Kaiba in this city and take the final card.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Obtaining the three God Cards will grant me the title of Pharaoh,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.08,0:09:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I will be freed from a curse lasting over a thousand years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.54,0:09:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I will obtain everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:10:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll triumph in this Duel in order to gain my lost memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.19,0:10:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.87,0:10:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(110,451)}Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(525,451)}Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I draw first!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.55,0:10:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.31,0:10:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set 1 reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\c&H0CCCEF&}Humanoid Slime{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.48,0:10:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.07,0:10:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,800 Attack {\c&H0CCCEF&}Humanoid Slime{\r} in Attack Mode?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.41,0:11:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Card Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's luring me into attacking...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to activate his reverse card Trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.96,0:11:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I'll use a Trap against a Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.01,0:11:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place 1 reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll Summon this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.80,0:11:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Illusion Beast Gazelle{\r} in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.60,0:11:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.23,0:11:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being awfully cautious to not attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.57,0:11:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, "cowardly" hits the nail on the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.90,0:11:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't defeat me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.57,0:11:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.16,0:11:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least don't die until you see the God Card {\c&H0000F5&\3c&H000000&}Osiris{\r} with your very own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an3}Just shut up\N already and draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.08,0:11:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon {\c&H0CCCEF&}Worm Drake{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll pull out a card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.51,0:12:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card {\c&H36A637&}Fusion{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.98,0:12:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Fusion Monster {\c&HBB238C&}Humanoid Drake{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}2200 Attack Points...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.49,0:12:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He fused Monsters into a more powerful Monster in order to attack fiercely this early?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.12,0:12:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Fusion Monsters can't attack in the turn they are Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.79,0:12:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm safe for the time being!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.38,0:12:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reverse card I have on the field, the one you thought was a Trap Card...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}wasn't{\i0} a Trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.34,0:12:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card {\c&H36A637&}Quick Attack{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.43,0:12:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.23,0:12:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It increases the speed of a fused Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and allows them to attack in the turn the appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.98,0:12:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't fear my opponent's cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the type to play it safe and not attack until I have the upper hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.58,0:13:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm different from cowards like you who are afraid of one messily reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.25,0:13:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HBB238C&}Humanoid Drake{\r}, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take apart {\c&H3896AE&}Illusion Beast Gazelle{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.01,0:13:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.39,0:13:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.31,0:13:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Fusion Release{\r}, is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the time you Summoned {\c&H0CCCEF&}Humanoid Slime{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you were going to fuse it into another Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.11,0:13:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew I was going to fuse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(327,208)}Sacrifice Summon, unlike Fusion Summon,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.41,0:13:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(304,195)}you can Summon a high-Attack Monster without wasting a turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.71,0:13:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've already planned your next move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already planned for the move after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.17,0:13:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your moves weren't strong enough to touch my Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.01,0:14:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were too weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.09,0:14:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was simply testing the waters on that turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cast a pebble to see how big a ripple you make...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to see your skills as a Duelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That move didn't even make a ripple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Duelist is like a vessel while strategy is water being poured into that vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The water takes the shape of the vessel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.86,0:14:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if the vessel is shallow, you can see the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.66,0:14:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the rumors state, you are a Duelist with great depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I were to cast the great stone I have hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it shall shatter the very vessel itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.80,0:14:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0000F5&}Osiris the Heaven Dragon{\r}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.42,0:14:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A great stone with the name of a {\i1}god{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.30,0:14:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.85,0:14:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.72,0:14:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This turn, I'll call another Monster to the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.85,0:14:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For now, I'll take out his Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.85,0:15:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next turn, I'll Sacrifice Summon {\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.36,0:15:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon {\c&H3896AE&}Magnet Warrior Beta{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.61,0:15:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Battle Phase!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.03,0:15:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Magnet Warrior Beta{\r}, attack {\c&H0CCCEF&}Worm Drake{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.66,0:15:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, {\c&H3896AE&}Illusion Beast Gazelle{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.91,0:15:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack {\c&H0CCCEF&}Humanoid Slime{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0CCCEF&}Worm Drake{\r} and {\c&H0CCCEF&}Humanoid Slime{\r} have been beaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.51,0:15:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now all the Monsters on his field have disappeared in that attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.56,0:15:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I now have the upper hand in this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.73,0:15:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't {\i1}get{\i0} it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.61,0:15:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who's been cornered!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.36,0:15:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.82,0:15:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I compared water to strategy before, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.66,0:15:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you that ultimate strategy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At times, water can become a shield that can protect against any attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at other times, it can become a sword capable of piercing the enemy's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Monster wields that power!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.76,0:16:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon {\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.76,0:16:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(389,421)}Revival Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.64,0:16:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.81,0:16:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.39,0:16:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an1\pos(50,458)}And one more\N card on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Slime Breeding Machine{\r}, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This device Special Summons 1 {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r} with 500 Attack and an Attribute of {\c&HE7271B&\3c&HFAF402&}Water{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I can't Summon another Monster but the {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Tokens{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.09,0:16:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until this Machine is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.21,0:16:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your aim is to sacrifice the Slimes on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Summon a high-level Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.85,0:16:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.81,0:16:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to Summon the God Card {\c&H0000F5&\3c&H000000&}Osiris the Heaven Dragon{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.81,0:17:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must sacrifice 3 Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.27,0:17:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0000F5&\3c&H000000&}Osiris the Heaven Dragon{\r}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.19,0:17:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's using this ability to Summon the Ultimate Monster...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be he has that card in his hand already?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.29,0:17:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.17,0:17:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.34,0:17:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, before he Summons {\c&H0000F5&\3c&H000000&}Osiris{\r}, I have no choice but to lower his Life to 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice the 2 Monsters I have on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the {\c&H0856C0&}Dragon Slayer Swordsman Buster Blader{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.11,0:17:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary swordsman known for slaying dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.45,0:17:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Sacrifice Summoned for {\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r}, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.83,0:17:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Attack {\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.25,0:18:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destructive Sword!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.96,0:18:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r} is beaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.39,0:18:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.14,0:18:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is {\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r}'s Regeneration Ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.48,0:18:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like water, no matter what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.61,0:18:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will return to the field unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.28,0:18:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regeneration Ability?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.11,0:18:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.45,0:18:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shapeless, invincible shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as this guy remains on the field, your Monsters' attacks can't touch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.00,0:18:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Monster that returns after being defeated?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.46,0:18:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Like this, I can't reduce his Life to 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.46,0:18:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing you can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ultimate strike combo designed to let God descend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.35,0:19:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only have...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3 turns left!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.52,0:19:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.35,0:19:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Slime Breeding Machine{\r}, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r} has appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.44,0:19:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also set a reverse card...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.45,0:19:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.12,0:19:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what are you gonna do, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.99,0:19:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every turn a {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r} is generated...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.91,0:19:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When 3 are made, you will sacrifice them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.50,0:19:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You plan to use them to Summon the God Card {\c&H0000F5&}Osiris the Heaven Dragon{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.05,0:19:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A good strategy with one flaw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}I have {\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r} on the field with 2600 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.89,0:19:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}Your {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r}'s Attack is 2100 points weaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.27,0:19:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If {\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r} defeats {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.23,0:19:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your Life will be reduced by 2100 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.19,0:19:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't make it to the third turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 2 turns, you're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:19:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.86,0:20:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Buster Blader{\r}, attack {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Token{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Permanent Trap Card, {\c&HB629E6&}Defender Slime{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.34,0:20:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H0856C0&}Revival Slime{\r} moved in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.63,0:20:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HB629E6&}Defender Slime{\r} is a card that forces the opponent to do battle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.51,0:20:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with only Monsters with the word "Slime" in their name as long as it remains in play.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.56,0:20:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I predicted you would try that, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.48,0:20:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I know my Life is wide open if you aim for the {\c&H3896AE&}Slime Tokens{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.99,0:20:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's 2 {\c&H3896AE&}Slimes{\r} now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.75,0:20:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On my next turn, God will descend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.42,0:21:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And to prepare for that, I've prepared a little something for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.97,0:21:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card {\c&H36A637&}Nightmare Steel Cage{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.12,0:21:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With {\c&H36A637&}Nightmare's Steelcage{\r}{\i1} in play, Yugi is sealed from attacking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the meantime, Malik is preparing to Summon the God Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.81,0:21:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After a long struggle, the God of the Sky {\c&H0000F5&}Osiris the Heaven Dragon {\c&HFFFFFF&}appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.56,0:22:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi, is there a way to defeat this Demon God Monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.49,0:22:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Osiris the Heaven Dragon"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.20,0:22:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.42,0:22:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I feel like I've been here, been in this place before
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.85,0:22:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the classroom shaded by the setting sun
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.27,0:22:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I laughed along and pointed with my too shortly cut bangs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.37,0:22:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Little by little, time keeps going
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.67,0:23:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My bangs now over my eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.84,0:23:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The sunset took everyone together
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.05,0:23:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure nothing changed while we were there
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.31,0:23:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.48,0:23:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I kept on searching for something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.65,0:23:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you understood such a senseless time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.82,0:23:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.54,0:23:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From here, always...

